COPS in Mutale are investigating the disappearance
of a 51-year-old man Tshilidzi Phanuel Mudau from Pile village. Limpopo cops spokesperson Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said Tshilidzi
was last seen on Saturday 7July. He did not inform anyone where he was going. Ngoepe said the family members have looked at all the places
normally visits without success. By the time of his disappearance he was wearing a khakhi
trouser, black leather jacket and was carrying a black laptop bag. "We request to anyone who knows his whereabouts
should contact Detective Warrant Officer Netill on 082 42777 28." Mutale Police Station on 015 976 8000, Sms Line number
32211 or Crime Stop Number on 08600 10111